  "text": "H. pylori reference strain NCTC 11637 and clinical isolate 968 were grown on Ham's F12 defined liquid media without the addition of enhancing growth factors. The medium was inoculated with cellular extracts obtained from Columbia blood agar (CBA) growth media. Cells were allowed to grow for 24 hours in a glass flask under microaerophilic atmosphere by gentile stirring at 37°C as described by Testerman et al. [CITATION_1] .",
